summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling its resolution 1599 (2005) on Timor-Leste,
Expressing deep concern over the 28/29 April incidents and the ensuing situation,
Acknowledging the Government of Timor-Leste's investigation into the incidents,
Reaffirming its commitment to stability in Timor-Leste,
 Decides to extend UNOTIL's mandate until 20 June 2006;
 Requests the Secretary-General to update the Council by 6 June 2006 on the situation and the UN's role;
 Encourages the Government to address the causes of violence with UNOTIL's assistance;
 Decides to remain seized of the matter.
